OL,3,CUK government must do more for Brits
OL,4,Cdetained in UAE, says campaign group
OL,6,FThe popular tourist destination is
OL,7,Fhome to stringent cybercrime laws,
OL,8,Fwhich impose strict penalties for
OL,9,Fdigital offences, such as spreading
OL,10,Ffalse information or rumours, invading
OL,11,Fsomeone's privacy, or accessing
OL,12,Fsomeone's computer system, without
OL,13,Fpermission.
OL,15,FPenalties in such cases can include up
OL,16,Fto two years in prison, fines ranging
OL,17,Ffrom AED 20,000 (around #4,000) to AED
OL,18,F200,000 (around #40,000), or both, and
OL,19,Fforeign nationals will also face
OL,20,Fdeportation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
